Gabriel Rivera Colon was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Gabriel Rivera Colon was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Waiver of Extradition and Order of Remand
Disposition Form; $3,500.00 cash bond revoked; Defendant remanded to Florida

Def appears in custody & w/Atty  State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Sandra Jo Giernoth for State. Interpreter Sarah Chwaszczewski present.  Atty DeJunco met with def a few days ago; def wishes to return to Florida and waive extradition. Def requested court date prior to the March 9 date previously set. Court questions defendant. Court revokes def's bond and orders def be remanded to Florida. Court executes Waiver of Extradition in triplicate.
Hearing for def to waive extradition scheduled with Atty DeJunco for Feb 26 at 10:00 am. Notice sent.

Def in person & by Atty Wilfred DeJunco of State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Mark David Bensen appeared for State. Interpreter, Mariana Kralewski appears by telephone. Def given complaint, and probable cause found. Def not disputing name or DOB as indicated on complaint. Def advised of charges and rights. Atty DeJunco requests def be admitted to bail to return to Florida on his own to contest the allegations there.  Hearing scheduled for March 9, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Extradition - fugitive from State of Florida, to-wit:  County of Osceola, for violating conditions of probation
